    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Is it worth attempting to optimize here before withdrawals are implemented, seems a little premature as we don't know how many exited validators there will be.  Currently there are 869 out of 431,496 validators exited, or a little over 0.2%.  I know that is the lower bound, but until we have some sort of idea of the real-world number we'd be doing a fair bit of work for what could be minimal gains.\r\n\r\nOnce capella goes live we should have some idea of the churn, which would help to inform the best way to approach reduction in size of the validator list.",
